Over a Boxplot of Age Vs Product we can see that we have ouliers in each product type but more outliers present in product type KP781,thus it is high false expectations that old age people tend to use it than reality.

Using describe method(difference between mean and median)

In [14]:
df_des=df.describe(include="all").T[['mean','50%']]
df_des.dropna(inplace=True)
df_des['Outliers']=np.abs(df_des['mean']-df_des['50%'])

8.PROBABILITY¶

MARGINAL PROBABILITY¶

Marginal Probability Over Fitness¶

From this we can say that for the product KP281 has fitness ranging 3,2,1 mostly.

From this we can say that for the product KP481 has fitness ranging 1,2,3 mostly.

From this we can say that for the product KP781 has fitness ranging 5 mostly.

Thus it can be infered that advanced options included Threadmill(KP781) results in highest fitness rate of 5.

It can be determined that probability of Fitness 5 buying a Threadmill KP781 is 0.93

Conditional Probability¶

Conditional Probability Over Fitness¶

Customer Profiling - Categorization of users.¶

From above analysis we can determine that

Usage-Miles:¶

Here we can see that a positive correlation betweem them with a correlation value of 0.76 which indicates that as usage increases number of miles walk/run per week also increases

Miles-Fitness:¶

Here we can see that a positive correlation betweem them with a correlation value of 0.79 which indicates that as number of miles walk/run per week increases Fitness also increases

Usage-Fitness:¶

Here we can see that a positive correlation betweem them with a correlation value of 0.67 which indicates that as Usage increases Fitness also increases

Age-Fitness:¶

Age and Fitness have weakly positive correlated since upto some age as age increases fitness increases after that as age increases fitness drastically decreases

Age-Usage:¶

Age and Usage have weakly positive correlated since upto some age as age increases usage increases after that as age increases usage decreases

Age-Income:¶

Age and Income are positively related with a positive correlation value of 0.52 indicates that as age increases income also increases

Product-Gender:¶

Over all the products of threadmill the KP281 is the type where both male and female show purchase rate in using and male show less purchase rate in using KP481 and female show very less interest in using KP781

Product-Income:¶

With Annual Income ranging over 20000 to 70000 show higher rate of interest to purchase KP281 and KP481 product type,whereas 50000 to 110000 Annual Income people interest to purchase product type KP781

Product-Usage:¶

People who use product of type KP281 and KP481 tend to use threadmill on an average of 2 to 4 times a week where as product type KP781 users tend to use 4 to 6 times on an average over a week

Product-Fitness:¶

People who use KP281 and KP481 results in fitness level of 3 at max where as people who use KP781 results in fitness level of 5

Product-Age:¶

KP281 product type has higher rate of purchase over the age (23-33) where 25%=23,50%=26,75%=33,min=15 and max=47

KP481 product type has higher rate of purchase over the age (24-33) where 25%=25,50%=26,75%=33,min=20 and max=45

KP781 product type has higher rate of purchase over the age (25-30) where 25%=25,50%=27,75%=30,min=22 and max=3

Product-Education:¶

Students of class 17 show higher purchase rate over KP781 and students of class 15 show higher purchase rate in KP281 and KP481

Product-MaritalStatus:¶

Even though Partnered people show higher purchase rate but in both single and partnered people show interest in KP281 product purchase

Product Vs Miles¶

People who tend to purchase product type of KP281 and KP481 walk/run around 10 to 150 miles each week. People who tend to purchase product type of KP781 walk/run around 100 to 250 miles each week
